sentence: Lumber Liquidators Holdings, Inc. ( LL ) was a big mover last session with its shares rising almost 9% on the day.
The upside came on a rating upgrade on the stock by an analyst at Cantor Fitzgerald, to "buy" from "hold."
The firm also raised its price target on Lumber Liquidators to $18 from $15.
This development led to far more shares changing hands yesterday than in a normal session.
This breaks the recent trend of the company as the stock is now trading above the volatile price range of $12.06 to $14.96 since Aug 5.
This multi-channel specialty retailer of hardwood flooring, and hardwood flooring enhancements and accessories has seen 8 negative estimate revisions in the last 30 days.
The Zacks Consensus Estimate has also moved lower over the same period.
This implies trouble down the road.
So make sure to keep an eye on this stock going forward to see if yesterday's rally can last.
Lumber Liquidators currently holds a Zacks Rank #5 (Strong Sell) while its Earnings ESP is 0.00%.
Investors interested in the building products space may, however, consider The Home Depot, Inc. ( HD ), which carries a Zacks Rank #2 (Buy).
